40:23.595 --> 40:25.510
Man, I just need
to get caught up.

40:25.553 --> 40:27.947
Plus, if there's
more opportunity here,

40:27.990 --> 40:29.557
then I can make
that transition.

40:29.601 --> 40:31.864
Look, you fall asleep
and have a spill,

40:31.907 --> 40:34.214
that's too dangerous,
Dante, I can't do that.

40:43.136 --> 40:44.920
I know this guy.
Oh, yeah?

40:44.964 --> 40:47.314
He works at Carl Steel.

40:47.357 --> 40:50.404
Okay. He hopped the fence

40:50.448 --> 40:53.233
and attacked me in the
middle of the night.

40:53.276 --> 40:55.627
Right over there
by where it happened?

40:55.670 --> 40:57.063
Yeah.
Know his name?

40:57.106 --> 40:58.673
No.

40:58.717 --> 41:00.806
So it wasn't
a four-wheeler accident.

41:00.849 --> 41:02.851
It wasn't that you
and the Furlbee girl

41:02.895 --> 41:05.114
got your signals crossed.
No.

41:05.158 --> 41:07.900
I'm sorry we lied to you.
I'm working for...

41:07.943 --> 41:12.034
Uh... I wasworking for her dad.

41:12.078 --> 41:13.949
So we weren't supposed
to be out there.

41:13.993 --> 41:17.692
So why you coming to me now,
changing your story?

41:17.736 --> 41:20.521
Because I didn't know
who it was before.

41:20.565 --> 41:22.480
You got experience
with the torches?

41:22.523 --> 41:25.134
I was hoping for some
opportunities for advancement.

41:25.178 --> 41:28.137
Uh, we start everybody as a
cutter unless you're a driver.

41:29.574 --> 41:31.184
You don't happen
to be a driver?

41:31.227 --> 41:33.186
What about crane work?

41:33.229 --> 41:35.318
Anything open there?

41:35.362 --> 41:37.103
Cranes are full right now.

41:37.146 --> 41:39.845
We would normally have openings,
but with the tariff stuff,

41:39.888 --> 41:42.369
China's taking less
of our scrap.

41:42.412 --> 41:45.154
I guess it's good for your boy
Bud Carl, though.

41:47.069 --> 41:49.898
I mean, we could train you up
for something

41:49.942 --> 41:51.944
if you were able to be here
during the day.

41:51.987 --> 41:53.946
I kind of have to be at night.

41:53.989 --> 41:57.515
Yeah, not much chance
for advancement at night.

41:59.342 --> 42:02.345
I'd like to find a way
for this to work out, though.

42:02.389 --> 42:03.782
I like you.

42:03.825 --> 42:05.566
You don't talk much,

42:05.610 --> 42:07.655
and that's one of my favorite
qualities in people.

42:11.746 --> 42:13.139
Hey.

42:13.182 --> 42:14.793
Hey.

42:14.836 --> 42:16.838
Racetrack savant?

42:16.882 --> 42:18.666
What?

42:18.710 --> 42:22.191
I, uh... I found some checks,
which made me curious,

42:22.235 --> 42:24.237
so I started snooping.

42:27.893 --> 42:31.766
I thought,
"Now, what kind of man

42:31.810 --> 42:35.465
has bug-out bags placed in three
different spots in his house?"

42:37.206 --> 42:40.035
And then I realized...

42:40.079 --> 42:42.385
"Every man I've ever known."

42:45.214 --> 42:47.042
You're gonna have to stay there.

42:47.086 --> 42:50.002
So, what do you want?

42:53.919 --> 42:57.618
Well, why don't we start
with who are you?

42:58.750 --> 43:01.622
Randall Abatsy?

43:01.666 --> 43:03.711
Or...

43:03.755 --> 43:07.280
are you Ronald Israel Ealy?

43:07.323 --> 43:08.760
Or...

43:08.803 --> 43:12.764
August Ray Bellflower?

43:12.807 --> 43:16.028
Maybe you are
Antwuan Carlos Fraley.

43:16.071 --> 43:17.682
You gonna turn me in?

43:17.725 --> 43:20.206
You know, you think
that I'm just a nice girl.

43:20.249 --> 43:22.425
I'm not pissed
'cause you're

43:22.469 --> 43:24.384
an immoral person.

43:24.427 --> 43:27.517
I'm pissed because you treated
me like the mark.

43:27.561 --> 43:30.477
And I told you that I'm not
the fucking mark.You're not the fucking mark.

43:32.740 --> 43:34.307
So my question is...

43:34.350 --> 43:35.438
I need you to stay down there.

43:35.482 --> 43:38.267
I already told you.

43:41.053 --> 43:42.576
Who are you?

43:42.620 --> 43:46.406
You know,
I couldn't figure out the con.

43:48.713 --> 43:51.933
Then I found your lease
for your Akron place.

43:51.977 --> 43:54.588
Under a different name,
of course.

43:54.632 --> 43:58.331
Just very lavish.

43:58.374 --> 44:01.377
I also found this list

44:01.421 --> 44:03.902
of Akron investors.

44:03.945 --> 44:05.730
And, just...

44:05.773 --> 44:07.906
I don't know, it made me sad,
'cause they all lost.

44:10.256 --> 44:12.388
But I think I figured it out.

44:12.432 --> 44:14.434
What'd you figure out?

44:14.477 --> 44:15.957
So you set up shop
in two nearby towns.

44:16.001 --> 44:18.525
Right? You throw parties,

44:18.568 --> 44:21.659
you pretend to be
a rich investor.
Hey.

44:21.702 --> 44:25.663
I'm a very rich investor.Okay.

44:25.706 --> 44:27.665
You pick a risky stock
to go up in one,

44:27.708 --> 44:30.450
and the same stock to go down
in the other.

44:30.493 --> 44:34.280
The people whose money you've
lost, you just, you split town.

44:34.323 --> 44:36.848
But the people
who you've made money for,

44:36.891 --> 44:39.938
you get them to invest a lot
more in the next thing.

44:39.981 --> 44:42.854
And then you split town
with their money.

44:42.897 --> 44:45.552
"Racetrack savant."

44:45.595 --> 44:47.641
I mean, oldest one in the book.

44:47.685 --> 44:49.208
S-So how do you know

44:49.251 --> 44:53.342
the names of cons
I've never even heard of?

44:53.386 --> 44:55.257
'Cause I saw my dad
at the racetrack.

44:55.301 --> 44:57.956
I mean, I've been watching
since I was, like, six.

44:59.827 --> 45:01.568
You know, sometimes
it was the difference

45:01.611 --> 45:03.962
